You'll very likely not see much snowfall in feb. Nainital is only 1936m above sea level and is on the lower reaches of the Himalayas. If snow is what you're looking for, 
head to a tiny little hamlet called Chopta. Its off-beat and is located midway between Kedarnath and Badrinath.
-----------------------------------
Can we visit Uttarakhand in January?
Among the unexplored winter destinations in Uttarakhand, 
Chopta Valley is the starting point for treks to Tungnath and Chandrashila and one of the best places to visit in Uttarakhand in January.
By road: Chopta is well connected by road to cities such as Rishikesh, Uttarkashi, Rudraprayag, and Pauri.
